ZH: 我们在比赛开始时都会起立唱国歌。
EN: We all stand up and sing the national anthem at the beginning of the game.

ZH: 这是我第一次在现场听国歌，感觉很激动。
EN: This is my first time hearing the national anthem live, I feel very excited.

ZH: 这首国歌唱出了民族的自豪感。
EN: This national anthem sings out the pride of the nation.

ZH: 我知道每个国家都有自己的国歌。
EN: I know that every country has its own national anthem.

ZH: 国歌是国家的象征。
EN: The national anthem is a symbol of the country.

ZH: 我们应该尊重并珍惜我们的国歌。
EN: We should respect and cherish our national anthem.

ZH: 刚刚唱过国歌，觉得很骄傲。
EN: Just sang the national anthem and felt very proud.

ZH: 能端详国歌的歌词是一种荣耀。
EN: Being able to recite the lyrics of the national anthem is an honor.

ZH: 很多人在听到国歌时都会站立。
EN: Many people stand up when they hear the national anthem.

ZH: 她的歌声让国歌显得更加雄壮。
EN: Her voice makes the national anthem sound even more majestic.

ZH: 这首国歌旋律优美动听。
EN: The melody of this national anthem is beautiful and pleasant.

ZH: 他们每天早晨都会播放国歌。
EN: They play the national anthem every morning.

ZH: 我们国家的国歌阳刚而富有力量。
EN: Our country's national anthem is masculine and powerful.

ZH: 每当国歌响起，大家都会起立致敬。
EN: Whenever the national anthem plays, everyone stands up to pay respects.

ZH: 他因为演唱国歌而成为国民英雄。
EN: He became a national hero for singing the national anthem.

ZH: 国歌是连接我们的情感的纽带。
EN: The national anthem is the bond that connects our emotions.

ZH: 那个国家的国歌我只听过一次。
EN: I've only heard that country's national anthem once.

ZH: 她的嗓音把国歌演绎得很动情。
EN: Her voice interprets the national anthem very emotionally.

ZH: 每个学生都应该学会唱国歌。
EN: Every student should learn how to sing the national anthem.

ZH: 这是我心中最喜欢的国歌之一。
EN: This is one of my favorite national anthems.
